Factor 2: Substantial 8-15. There is, or will be, an inability to carry out the majority of essential personal care or domestic routines.  A person needs daily or continuous help and support with essential activities of daily living, whose care or living arrangements will break down or become unsafe without provision of community care services.  A person who is, or will be, unable to manage their own essential activities of daily living without the provision of community care services to support them to sustain their caring role.